eNCA's senior reporter Siphamandla Goge reported from Nelspruit. Courtesy of #DStv403 NELSPRUIT - Former State Security Minister Bongani Bongo is back in the Nelspruit magistrate's court on Thursday morning. He faces charges of corruption, fraud, theft and money laundering. READ: Corruption case against Bongani Bongo dismissed The charges are linked to alleged dodgy land deals to the value of over R120-million. The cases allegedly took place while Bongo was an official in the Mpumalanga Human Settlements Department.